Create GUI for chatbot
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no GUI for the chatbot and some logic can be better made to be OOP style.

With a GUI, it is easier for user to key in their commands. With more OOP, the code base is easier to read.

Use JavaFX to create the UI. Create Command and its corresponding subclasses to make the code more OOP.

JavaFX is utilised as it is incorporating well with Gradle. OOP is used to make the code more bearable to read.

Parser and TaskList Test cases were also modified to test the changed code in the respective classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add checkstyle to enforce coding standards
commitResults.messageBody:
The code base does not have a code enforcer to ensure coding standard is adhered to

Reason for change is so that cleaner code can be standardised

Add checkstyle plug-ins into build gradle to introduce checkstyle to enforce coding standard

The plug-ins are added to the build gradle file so that gradle can help automate this checking process

commitResults.messageBody:

Assertions need to be introduced to define assumptions about the program state so that the runtime can verify them

Add assert keywords to certain parts of the code

This is to ensure that some variables need to be of a certain state for the program to continue smoothly
